title.narrative: 1.7. ESSENTIAL CHILD HEALTH SERVICES

description.narrative: National capacity enhanced to provide access to essential high-impact child health interventions, which contributes to Child Health, Child Health (Covid), Cross-Sectoral Early Childhood Development, Early Childhood Development, Maternal And Newborn Health, Maternal And Newborn Health (Covid), Prevention And Response Services For Violence Against Children, Prevention Of Stunting And Other Forms Of Malnutrition. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Children, especially the most deprived, access and utilize quality and equitable protection, education, health and nutrition services

title.narrative: National capacity enhanced to provide access to essential high-impact child health interventions

description.narrative: National capacity was enhanced through promotion and development of an online modality on Infant and Young Child Feeding, immunization, and early childhood development. ;Capacity of healthcare workers on infection prevention and control and case management was strengthened in response to the COVID-19 pandemic. ;Mothers and children affected by the escalation of the conflict in and beyond the Nagorno-Karabakh region were provided with essential health care and nutrition counselling services through establishment of Baby-Friendly Rooms. UNICEF continued to support the ongoing preliminary healthcare reforms and implementation of the mandatory health insurance through strengthened coordination and partnership with various health authorities.; | Status:Met | As-of Date:18/01/2021
